          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bring a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Crack the <strong>eggs</strong> gently into the water and leave them for 3 min</p><p>Once done, gently transfer the<strong> eggs</strong> with a slotted spoon to <strong>kitchen paper </strong>or a clean tea-towel and season them with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – these are your <strong>poached eggs</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
